Read and apply wow/task/RULES.md first.

Perform a weekly wow maintenance pass.

Do this in order:
1. Run bash wow/check-workflow.sh; fix structural/naming issues only
   (checker failures are safe to fix autonomously)
2. Run completed compaction for v2 leaves:
    - Source leaves: `completed/yyyymmdd-hhmm_<module>_<task-slug>/`
    - Group by day+module into containers:
      `completed/yyyymmdd-<module>_<essence-slug>/`
    - Derive `<essence-slug>` using canonical policy (same as
      `wow/task/completed-close-bundle`):
      1) explicit summary override (`essence=` / `Essence:`),
      2) summary title (`summary=` / `Summary:`) when provided,
      3) latest leaf plan title fallback,
      4) stable fallback `daily-rollup` only when semantic sources are empty
    - Normalize essence deterministically: lowercase ASCII, non-alnum-to-dash,
      collapse dashes, trim edges, max length 48, deterministic truncation
    - Do not create new `_bundle`-essence containers; existing `_bundle`
      containers may be reused for compatibility and reported as migration
      candidates
    - If a new container name collides on the same day+module with a different
      semantic source, append deterministic `-x<8hex>` suffix from canonical
      source hash
    - Keep leaf folder names immutable (move only; never rename)
    - Reuse existing container for the same day+module if present
    - Create/update one markdown summary artifact in each touched container
   - Reconcile bundle registry (`wow/completed/.bundle-registry.tsv`) for
     each touched day+module key using:
     `day-module-key<TAB>folder-name<TAB>created-at<TAB>source-item-path`
     (keep existing matching entries; append missing entries; report
     conflicts, do not auto-rewrite conflicting rows)
3. List active items; flag stale ones (Updated older than 7 days)
4. For each stale item, recommend: keep active, complete, or dismiss
5. Review queue ordering; suggest top 3 execution candidates
6. Verify completed layout invariants:
   - v2 leaves and v2 containers follow naming contract
   - nested leaves under containers keep day/module alignment
   - legacy folders remain accepted but are reported for optional migration
   - no empty completed folders
   - bundle registry row for each touched day+module key resolves to exactly
     one container folder path
7. Re-run bash wow/check-workflow.sh

Constraints:
- Fix only structural issues (checker failures) autonomously
- Do not move files between workflow states without my approval
- Moving completed leaves into completed containers is allowed (same state).
- Present state-transition recommendations as a list for me to approve

Report:
- Checker results (before and after)
- Completed compaction actions (created/reused containers, moved leaves, summaries)
- Bundle registry actions (reused/appended rows, conflicts)
- Legacy completed folders skipped for manual mapping (if any)
- Active summary with staleness flags
- Recommendation per stale item
- Queue priority ranking
- Structural fixes applied (if any)
